{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959618,"pPcc":"SAT#Q","questionId":"5dc386fb","skill_cd":"Q.E.","score_band_range_cd":7,"skill_desc":"Probability and conditional probability","createDate":1691007959618,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Problem-Solving and Data Analysis","ibn":"022848-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"Q","uId":"b1ca7524-5430-4f33-9c18-5f68968a3f86","difficulty":"H"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"022848-DC","section":"Math","body":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference \" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p1\">\n\t<div class=\"passage \">\n\t\t<div class=\"prose style:1 \">\n\t\t\t<p class=\"passage_para \">The table below shows the distribution of US states according to whether they have a state-level sales tax and a state-level income tax.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<table class=\"table_WithBorder\">\n\t\t\t\t<caption>2013 State-Level Taxes</caption>\n\t\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-153694c7-8fa3-4e23-94a4-6ea6e2e697de\">&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-e5a53952-9288-40e0-ac19-cafecda65b9b\">State sales tax</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-10ebc204-0eda-4bce-ba75-826a9b8a2a82\">No state sales tax</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-90f074ad-6769-4a50-ae37-618ca7ff7b31\">State income tax</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-97ba8e95-d3bf-4293-b928-e12feb1f5419\">39</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-1b3bda3e-5a56-499a-a798-bbd993270702\">4</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-c1409411-06b0-4363-89b8-171abff0b8c0\">No state income tax</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-43b1ecd9-27b9-4264-9eac-617d6bce776a\">6</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"tcp-6256a8c4-7f90-4037-ae03-64c4afd368b8\">1</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t\t</table>\n\n\t\t\t<p class=\"passage_para \">&nbsp;</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">To the nearest tenth of a percent, what percent of states with a state-level sales tax do not have a state-level income tax?</p>\n","answer":{"style":"Multiple Choice","choices":{"a":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">6.0%</p>\n"},"b":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">12.0%</p>\n"},"c":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">13.3%</p>\n"},"d":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">14.0%</p>\n"}},"correct_choice":"c","rationale":"<p>Choice C is correct. The sum of the number of states with a state-level sales tax is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"39 plus 6, equals 45\"></span>. Of these states, 6 don&rsquo;t have a state-level income tax. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"6 over 45, equals 0 point 1 3 3 3 dot dot dot\"></span>, or about 13.3%, of states with a state-level sales tax don&rsquo;t have a state-level income tax.<p><br>\n\tChoice A is incorrect. This is the number of states that have a state-level sales tax and no state-level income tax. Choice B is incorrect. This is the percent of states that have a state-level sales tax and no state-level income tax. Choice D is incorrect. This is the percent of states that have no state-level income tax.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"}}}